# Frontend Conventions

## Component Structure
- Functional components only, no class components.
- One component per file. File name matches component name (PascalCase).
- Pages go in `src/pages/`, reusable UI pieces in `src/components/`.
- Extract logic into custom hooks in `src/hooks/` when a component has more than simple state.

## Platform
- This app runs in a smartphone browser, used one-handed at the gym. Design for this always.
- Minimum tap target size: 48px height on all interactive elements.
- Use `inputMode="numeric"` on all number inputs (weight, reps, rest time) so the numeric keyboard opens on mobile.
- No hover-only interactions — everything must work by touch.
- Default viewport target: 390px wide (iPhone-size). Test at this width.

## Tailwind
- Mobile-first: start with base styles for 390px, use `sm:` / `md:` breakpoints to scale up.
- No inline `style` props — use Tailwind classes only.
- Keep className strings readable; split to multiple lines if they exceed ~80 chars.

## Data Fetching
- All API calls go through utility functions in `src/utils/api.js` — no raw `fetch` calls inside components.
- Use `useEffect` + local state for now (no external data-fetching library for MVP).

## State
- React Context for shared state. No Redux or Zustand unless complexity demands it.
- Keep context providers close to where they're needed — don't dump everything in a root provider.
